span class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003ERadius\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E-\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E).\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Enormalized\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n            \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evessel\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003ESetWorldVelocity\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Enorth \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E*\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E100\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E);\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\n            \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evessel\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EUpdatePosVel\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E();\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\u00A0 Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T13:59:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to manipulate the vessel orbit.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOrbit.UpdateFromStateVectors() should be the most straightforward way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arrowstar","CreatedById":2521,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T14:07:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262160\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679234353\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gotmachine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Gotmachine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to manipulate the vessel orbit.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOrbit.UpdateFromStateVectors() should be the most straightforward way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat, thank you.\u00A0 I see that method in the API documentation.\u00A0 Any idea what reference frame those position and velocity Vector3d objects are relative to?\u00A0 And do I just get the Orbit from the Vessel\u0027s OrbitDriver object?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T14:26:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262168\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679234859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arrowstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Arrowstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny idea what reference frame those position and velocity Vector3d objects are relative to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom memory, they are relative to the current body frame, but really not sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262168\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679234859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arrowstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Arrowstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd do I just get the Orbit from the Vessel\u0027s OrbitDriver object?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes that should work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arrowstar","CreatedById":2521,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T15:00:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679235977\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gotmachine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, Gotmachine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom memory, they are relative to the current body frame, but really not sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes that should work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you say relative to the current body frame, you mean an inertial frame whose center is the center of the celestial body being orbited?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T15:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262199\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679238049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arrowstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Arrowstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you say relative to the current body frame, you mean an inertial frame whose center is the center of the celestial body being orbited?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t remember and I\u0027m too lazy to check \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would suggest doing a github search for \u0022\u003C/span\u003EUpdateFromStateVectors\u003Cspan\u003E\u0022, that should give you plenty of examples of how it should be used.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arrowstar","CreatedById":2521,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T22:30:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262210\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679238963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gotmachine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Gotmachine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t remember and I\u0027m too lazy to check \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would suggest doing a github search for \u0022\u003C/span\u003EUpdateFromStateVectors\u003Cspan\u003E\u0022, that should give you plenty of examples of how it should be used.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I\u0027ve given this a go, and all that happens when I execute the is the spacecraft twitches a bit.\u00A0 It\u0027s like the orbit gets set and then is immediately reversed.\u00A0 I\u0027m not sure what to do about it.\u00A0 Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee 0:09 of this video for an example of what I mean. Sorry for all the dinging sounds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://vimeo.com/manage/videos/809574842/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://vimeo.com/manage/videos/809574842/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T22:56:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo manipulate the orbit you likely need to pack the vessel first with Vessel.GoOnRails().\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis being said, I noticed in the video that the vessel is in-atmo.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure what you\u0027re trying to achieve, but if you\u0027re trying to set the vessel velocity while in atmo, I\u0027m not sure this is actually doable with orbit manipulation.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou will likely have to manually teleport the vessel first, then apply a velocity to all the parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI highly suggest that you check the source of existing mods doing similar things, HyperEdit is the main one coming to mind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}